	(text "EN = Active low enable: When this pin is high, all switches are turned off. When this pin is low,\nSEL pin controls the signal path selection. Internal 6 MΩ pull-down to GND."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 248.412 157.734 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
		)
		(uuid "04fc044e-03d5-4b45-a64d-e5b5b48f4378")
	)
	(text "Overengineered, only the N-Channel is neccesary."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 293.624 349.504 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 2 2)
			)
		)
		(uuid "089a0539-db8b-4f6d-a662-bc4294a3f1ac")
	)
	(text "FT2232H with a 12 MHz ± 0.003% crystal. In this case loading\ncapacitors should to be added between OSCI, OSCO and GND as shown. A value of 27 pF is shown as the\ncapacitor in the example - this will be good for many crystals but it is recommended to select the loading\ncapacitor value based on the manufacturer's recommendations wherever possible. It is recommended to\nuse a parallel cut type crystal.\nIt is also possible to use a 12 MHz Oscillator with the FT2232H. In this case the output of the oscillator\nwould drive OSCI, and OSCO should be left unconnected. The oscillator must have a CMOS output drive\ncapability."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 55.118 120.65 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1 1)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "1cbd77db-cbe9-466f-9964-33ad4ee4481d")
	)
